vectorData.altText: 14. The spinal cord dorsal columns carry sensations of fine touch, vibration and conscious proprioception sensations from the _______________ side of the body.

That's right!  Primary sensory neurons in the spinal cord DC carry sensations of fine touch, proprioception from the ipsilateral side of the body. Decussation happens at the level of secondary sensory neurons in the medulla.
That is incorrect. Click here      to learn the answer, then come back to try again.

1° neurons:
cell bodies in DRG in the PNS
axons project to CNS via dorsal roots, and ascend in the ipsilateral fasciculus cuneatus (FC)
synapse onto:

3°neurons:
cell bodies in the VP thalamus, axons project to:
 1° somatosensory cortex in the postcentral gyrus
Fine Touch, Vibration Sense & Conscious from the arm.

2° neurons: 
cell bodies in the nucleus cuneatus (NC) of the medulla
axons decussate, ascend contralaterally in the medial lemniscus (ML)
